A similar situation was with natural gas, as EU countries have turned to other energy supplies.

In the first quarter of 2022, Russia was the largest supplier to the EU with a part of 38.8%, but in the first quarter of 2023 Russia's share fell by 21.4%.

As for liquefied natural gas, Russia(18,1%)was the second detachment of the EU supplier after the US(48,6%)In the first quarter of 2022.If compare with the first quarter of 2023, the share of Russia fell by 4.9%._Фото: qiujiu song, shutterstock_

